                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="44992" author="furlongm" created="Mon, 17 Sep 2012 01:24:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is there any chance of this being backported to the 2.1 branch? Currently can&apos;t use SRP on the 2.1 branch using the whamcloud built rpms:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ib_srp: disagrees about version of symbol ib_unregister_client&lt;br/&gt;
ib_srp: Unknown symbol ib_unregister_client&lt;br/&gt;
ib_srp: Unknown symbol ib_wq&lt;br/&gt;
ib_srp: disagrees about version of symbol ib_fmr_pool_unmap&lt;br/&gt;
ib_srp: Unknown symbol ib_fmr_pool_unmap&lt;br/&gt;
ib_srp: disagrees about version of symbol ib_create_cq&lt;br/&gt;
ib_srp: Unknown symbol ib_create_cq&lt;br/&gt;
ib_srp: disagrees about version of symbol ib_create_fmr_pool&lt;br/&gt;
ib_srp: Unknown symbol ib_create_fmr_pool&lt;br/&gt;
ib_srp: disagrees about version of symbol ib_dereg_mr&lt;br/&gt;
ib_srp: Unknown symbol ib_dereg_mr&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="44045" author="pjones" created="Fri, 31 Aug 2012 11:28:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Landed for 2.3&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="40342" author="apittman" created="Mon, 11 Jun 2012 09:23:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;When using external OFED it is not possible to use the inkernel srp module, we currently patch lbuild to build srp as part of the OFED build.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="40128" author="ihara" created="Wed, 6 Jun 2012 11:14:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That information seems to be a little bit old. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,3049&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,3049&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve tested lbuild with &quot;--with-srp-mod&quot; to latest OFED (OFED-1.5.4.1) on RHEL5.7 and RHEL6.2&apos;s kernel with master branch and compiling of kernel-ib was no problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="40028" author="brian" created="Tue, 5 Jun 2012 13:27:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;IIRC, we were advised by upstream (i.e. OFA) that we should be using the iscsi provided by the kernel when we found problems building various parts of the OFED stack.  See &lt;a href=&quot;http://bugs.openfabrics.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=1764&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://bugs.openfabrics.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=1764&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
